A large-scale production method of fabricating binary transition-
metal oxide yolk–shell powders by applying a simple spray-drying
process was proposed. The preparation of precursor powders with
lowhygroscopicity, a dense structure, and a spherical shape by apply-
ing dextrin as an appropriate carbon source material was key to the
preparation of these powders. The optimumpost-treatment temper-
